#### Digging Deeper

Now that we have time periods in which certain broad sectors were highly priced, we can repeat the above at a more granular level. In the following, we consider only *Large Cap* and *Ultra-Large Cap* as there are fewer companies in each bucket when aggregating at a more granular sector level:

::: panel-tabset


```{.r .cell-code}
classification_1_vec <- r3000_raw %>% distinct(classification_1) %>% pull()

start_tbl <- r3000_nested %>% 
